Excuse me!

29:25.972 --> 29:28.433
No rush, I was just saying. It was a joke.

29:28.516 --> 29:30.143
-No, please.
-No, I'm going.

29:30.226 --> 29:31.686
No, really.

29:31.770 --> 29:32.604
Have you got it?

29:32.687 --> 29:33.897
-I'll sit here.
-No, me.

29:33.980 --> 29:35.482
You move your feet…

29:35.565 --> 29:36.399
Careful.

29:36.483 --> 29:38.359
Slowly. The wicker is super fragile.

29:38.443 --> 29:39.944
I'll sit very carefully.

29:40.028 --> 29:42.614
-Dad, don't exaggerate.
-Your coffee, Bobby.

29:43.198 --> 29:44.199
Thanks so much.

29:44.741 --> 29:47.076
Well, Bobby,
we have something to tell you.

29:47.160 --> 29:48.953
-What?
-We're married.

29:49.037 --> 29:50.872
How cool! Congratulations! When?

29:50.955 --> 29:53.041
-No.
-I mean, we're going to.

29:53.124 --> 29:53.958
It will be here.

29:54.459 --> 29:55.335
-Here?
-Yes.

29:55.418 --> 29:57.128
The dining room? You need more chairs.

29:57.837 --> 30:01.299
No. In Mérida, at a wonderful estate.
It's just dreamy. You have no idea.

30:01.382 --> 30:03.384
Guess who's making my dress?

30:03.468 --> 30:04.761
Um…

30:05.345 --> 30:06.805
-Who?
-Guess!

30:08.139 --> 30:11.059
-Mitsy.
-No. Sara Escribano.

30:11.142 --> 30:13.770
Even better! Congratulations! So cool!

30:13.853 --> 30:14.687
Wow!

30:14.771 --> 30:16.064
Marriage is terrible.

30:16.689 --> 30:17.649
What's up with you?

30:17.732 --> 30:18.608
Seriously, Dad?

30:19.275 --> 30:20.610
Mom, please do something.

30:20.693 --> 30:22.403
You'll never get married, right?

30:23.238 --> 30:24.823
Promise you'll never get married.

30:24.906 --> 30:26.282
Give me your word, Roberto.

30:30.119 --> 30:30.954
Sacni.

30:31.037 --> 30:32.455
Good morning, Sara Escribano.

30:32.539 --> 30:34.749
We need to hurry
to make my sister's dress,

30:34.833 --> 30:38.336
two hundred million accessories,
and a collection for Fashion Fest.

30:39.212 --> 30:40.088
You accepted?

30:44.843 --> 30:45.844
Yes!

30:47.095 --> 30:48.429
We're going to get it all.

30:52.684 --> 30:53.977
Did you ask for an advance?

30:57.021 --> 30:57.981
Fuck.

31:15.290 --> 31:16.624
Hello, what are you doing?

31:17.584 --> 31:18.668
Well I never.

31:42.817 --> 31:45.987
All I want to do is dance

31:46.070 --> 31:47.155
Aarón?

31:47.238 --> 31:48.323
Forever

31:48.948 --> 31:49.949
Is that a serenade?

31:50.033 --> 31:51.951
With you until morning comes

31:57.040 --> 31:58.416
They never took off

31:58.499 --> 32:01.294
They never left the nest

32:02.629 --> 32:03.755
Hey!

32:04.339 --> 32:05.173
What's up?

32:05.798 --> 32:06.633
What's up?

32:07.675 --> 32:08.676
Too loud?

32:09.260 --> 32:10.511
Yeah, I'm going to sleep.

32:11.429 --> 32:12.263
Okay.

32:12.347 --> 32:13.181
Okay.

32:14.724 --> 32:17.143
You're sleeping
on the first floor tonight, okay?

32:17.226 --> 32:18.394
-Okay.
-Okay.

32:19.896 --> 32:23.399
Just, make sure to close up the back room.

32:23.483 --> 32:25.568
-Yeah, okay.
-Where you guys sleep.

32:26.069 --> 32:28.071
-Okay.
-But seriously, close it up well.

32:29.072 --> 32:29.906
Okay.

32:31.616 --> 32:32.617
Good night, Sari.

32:32.700 --> 32:33.534
Sleep tight.

32:34.118 --> 32:35.578
-Bye. You too.
-See you tomorrow.

32:36.871 --> 32:38.331
-Okay.
-Okay, from there.

32:38.414 --> 32:41.250
I want to go out that evening
And make a miracle happen

32:41.334 --> 32:44.796
I want to pluck a star from the sky
To light my cigarette with

32:44.879 --> 32:46.130
Turn the world in my hand

32:46.214 --> 32:48.257
Like it were a basketball

32:48.341 --> 32:51.803
I want to keep your smile in my mind
Like when you had braces

32:53.721 --> 32:56.224
Baby, wait, I never wore braces.

32:58.101 --> 33:00.603
It's a metaphor.

33:01.854 --> 33:03.356
Because your smile

33:03.439 --> 33:04.399
is perfect…

33:11.614 --> 33:12.573
Can we talk now?

33:28.715 --> 33:30.091
Sorry.

33:30.174 --> 33:31.884
-Did I scratch you?
-What?

33:32.427 --> 33:33.970
I mean, yeah, but why?

33:34.053 --> 33:35.471
I wanted to give you a kiss.

33:35.972 --> 33:37.598
-Ah.
-Sorry.

33:37.682 --> 33:38.683
No, it's fine.

33:39.767 --> 33:41.436
Maybe you could be the big spoon?

33:42.270 --> 33:43.688
-No, not right now.
-No, yes.

33:43.771 --> 33:45.440
-No, wait.
-No, yes.

33:45.523 --> 33:46.357
No.

33:48.818 --> 33:49.986
Are you okay?

33:51.320 --> 33:53.573
What do we need to talk about now?

33:53.656 --> 33:55.658
About the same thing
we tried to talk about.

33:55.742 --> 33:57.201
-I don't want to.
-Smells great.

33:57.285 --> 33:58.661
-Coffee?
-How are you?

33:58.745 --> 34:00.246
-Hi, Dad.
-Want some eggs?

34:00.329 --> 34:03.082
-Good morning. Coffee?
-Yes, Ma. Please. With cream.

34:03.166 --> 34:05.501
-Eggs, too, right?
-Yes, with no onion.

34:05.585 --> 34:07.170
No, like this it has a ton--

34:07.253 --> 34:09.213
No onion is better. Just look.

34:09.297 --> 34:10.214
Hey, and Lucy?

34:10.298 --> 34:12.008
She stayed at a hotel.

34:12.091 --> 34:13.551
She didn't want to wake you.

34:14.177 --> 34:16.095
-What? She didn't sleep here?
-Look…

34:16.179 --> 34:18.890
-No. Did you say sugar?
-She didn't sleep in the shop?

34:19.640 --> 34:20.475
No.

34:21.309 --> 34:22.977
-What?
-What happened?

34:23.061 --> 34:23.895
Oh no.

34:24.562 --> 34:25.813
Oh no. They were exposed.

34:26.355 --> 34:27.273
They were exposed.

34:27.815 --> 34:30.026
I couldn't rinse them
and they were all exposed.

34:30.526 --> 34:31.569
No, no way.

34:32.195 --> 34:33.029
Oh no.

34:33.696 --> 34:34.655
Oh no.

34:34.739 --> 34:36.449
-What's up?
-What happened?

34:36.532 --> 34:38.201
What's going on, Sara? Dear God!

34:38.284 --> 34:39.118
What happened?

34:39.202 --> 34:41.079
You should have stayed here

34:41.162 --> 34:44.457
and closed up like I had asked you to.
It was very simple.

34:44.540 --> 34:46.125
They were very easy instructions.

34:46.209 --> 34:47.835
Just close the door.

34:47.919 --> 34:49.212
I told you last night.

34:49.295 --> 34:51.214
Because it lets the light in.

34:51.297 --> 34:52.173
These were exposed,

34:52.256 --> 34:53.299
they're fucked.

34:53.382 --> 34:55.468
But, Sara, you never told us.

34:55.551 --> 34:57.970
Well, of course!
A star couldn't sleep here.

34:58.054 --> 35:00.306
My bedbugs might bite them.

35:00.389 --> 35:01.224
What? No.

35:01.307 --> 35:02.141
Good morning.

35:02.225 --> 35:03.226
Son of a bitch!

35:03.309 --> 35:04.185
Good morning.

35:05.937 --> 35:08.022
I knew it was stupid.

35:09.148 --> 35:11.818
It was foolish of me
to accept Fashion Fest.

35:11.901 --> 35:13.277
I knew it and I did it anyway.

35:13.361 --> 35:14.821
I did it anyway, shit!

35:15.321 --> 35:16.989
Fuck everything!

35:20.451 --> 35:21.994
She gets that temper from Grandma.

35:22.078 --> 35:23.663
Forget about your bridal gown!

35:23.746 --> 35:24.789
Yikes.

35:24.872 --> 35:26.541
I don't think she had breakfast.

35:33.256 --> 35:37.176
Don't ask me

35:37.802 --> 35:41.222
If it's gone or not

35:42.682 --> 35:47.645
Don't ask me

35:48.271 --> 35:50.690
If it's over

35:52.650 --> 35:55.695
Because I have nothing to say

35:56.362 --> 35:59.198
I have nothing to tell you

35:59.282 --> 36:01.659
But since you've gone

36:02.243 --> 36:05.163
I haven't stopped crying, yeah

36:05.746 --> 36:07.498
Sara, you can't give up that easy.

36:07.582 --> 36:10.960
If I told you all the times I've failed…
Look at this one.

36:12.753 --> 36:13.796
"Chihuahua."

36:14.672 --> 36:16.924
-You look like a chihuahua.
-Very funny.

36:17.008 --> 36:18.634
No way!

36:19.218 --> 36:21.179
-Seriously…
-You also look like a bird.

36:21.262 --> 36:23.723
You look more
like a bird than a chihuahua, really.

36:23.806 --> 36:25.183
A bird looking for grubs.

36:26.893 --> 36:27.727
It's very good.

36:27.810 --> 36:30.062
You'll have to send it to me, please.

36:31.397 --> 36:32.231
What?

36:32.315 --> 36:36.235
There was going to be a protest
to cancel your concert?

36:36.319 --> 36:37.153
Yeah.

36:38.529 --> 36:41.240
It was a joke,
but, like, 1,000 assholes showed up.

36:41.324 --> 36:42.909
No! They showed up?

36:42.992 --> 36:43.826
Yeah.

36:43.910 --> 36:45.995
So you're more fucked than I am.

36:46.078 --> 36:46.913
I told you.

36:48.247 --> 36:51.000
Look, remember this song?

36:51.834 --> 36:52.668
Which?

36:53.753 --> 36:55.755
You're within me

36:56.505 --> 36:58.216
Until the final beat of my heart

36:58.299 --> 36:59.300
Ah, yes, I remember.

36:59.800 --> 37:02.720
In the light of your balcony

37:02.803 --> 37:05.932
In every minute, at every corner

37:06.015 --> 37:06.849
I like it.

37:06.933 --> 37:07.767
A lot.

37:09.310 --> 37:11.229
Some like it, some think it's shit.

37:11.938 --> 37:14.649
And some scream for it at concerts.

37:16.400 --> 37:17.235
Yeah?

37:18.069 --> 37:18.903
And you?

37:19.487 --> 37:20.571
And me?

37:20.655 --> 37:21.572
Do you like it?

37:22.990 --> 37:23.950
I like it a lot.

37:25.117 --> 37:26.244
I wrote it for you.

37:27.578 --> 37:28.454
For me?

37:29.413 --> 37:30.248
Why?

37:33.125 --> 37:34.502
Because you're my…

37:35.670 --> 37:36.754
best friend.

37:37.380 --> 37:40.049
And well, it doesn't matter
what others think.

37:44.011 --> 37:45.429
So what does matter?

37:46.681 --> 37:47.848
What you feel, here.

37:48.891 --> 37:49.809
Honey!

37:49.892 --> 37:50.851
-Come on!
-What?

37:50.935 --> 37:52.270
Go to sleep.

37:54.772 --> 37:55.898
I know.

37:55.982 --> 37:57.900
But he's your sister's fiance.

37:58.943 --> 38:01.279
Enough. My broken heart's plenty, Sara.

38:01.862 --> 38:02.697
Careful.

38:04.448 --> 38:05.283
Come.

38:06.742 --> 38:07.576
Go to sleep.

38:08.244 --> 38:09.662
Let's go to sleep. Here.

38:27.263 --> 38:28.097
Lucy.

38:29.724 --> 38:30.599
Are you okay?

38:34.061 --> 38:35.813
I don't think he wants to marry me.

38:38.065 --> 38:40.026
He only ever wrote songs for her.

38:42.403 --> 38:43.487
Her?

38:43.988 --> 38:45.990
His first love.

38:46.073 --> 38:49.452
The one that will be within him
until the final beat of his heart.

38:54.165 --> 38:56.751
Do you know who she is?

38:58.419 --> 38:59.253
I don't.

39:00.588 --> 39:03.215
Maybe a Spanish lover,

39:04.425 --> 39:06.844
or some Hungarian summer fling.

39:13.476 --> 39:15.436
Though, sometimes, I think it could be…

39:19.690 --> 39:23.402
that no one in the whole world
would want to spend their life with me.

39:27.156 --> 39:28.616
You're joking, right?

39:32.328 --> 39:33.162
Lucy…

39:34.872 --> 39:36.874
you're a diamond in the rough.

39:38.793 --> 39:40.586
And you have a huge heart.

39:41.796 --> 39:45.424
Anyone would be lucky
to spend their life with you.

39:48.719 --> 39:49.804
Starting with you?

39:50.304 --> 39:51.639
Starting with me,

39:52.348 --> 39:53.182
sis.

39:55.643 --> 39:56.977
Now can I rinse off?

39:57.061 --> 39:57.895
Hey.

40:00.940 --> 40:02.942
So will you make my dress?

40:06.028 --> 40:06.862
Obviously.

40:11.826 --> 40:12.660
Baby!

40:13.411 --> 40:14.245
Hi!

40:14.328 --> 40:15.162
How'd it go?

40:15.246 --> 40:16.539
-Very well.
-Yeah? Nice?

40:21.085 --> 40:22.545
-How are you?
-Good.

40:22.628 --> 40:23.838
-Good?
-Here.

40:23.921 --> 40:24.755
Look, touch.

40:24.839 --> 40:27.925
-It finally cooled down.
-They gave us a delicious facial.

40:28.008 --> 40:28.843
Touch it.

40:29.343 --> 40:31.595
-See? My love, I'm talking to you.
-Yeah.

40:39.228 --> 40:41.188
The most important thing is your peace.

40:42.398 --> 40:44.525
Your tranquility, your…

40:46.026 --> 40:49.697
Your stability,
because you're part of the…

40:51.115 --> 40:52.950
The show, as like--

40:53.033 --> 40:54.660
My love, you were sleeping.

40:55.286 --> 40:56.120
Sleep.

40:56.745 --> 40:58.205
Okay? Sleep tight.

41:08.549 --> 41:10.468
You have to stop, Sara.

41:12.720 --> 41:16.348
…we'll go to the top

41:16.432 --> 41:20.186
Of your favorite cloud

41:20.269 --> 41:22.313
And from there

41:24.815 --> 41:29.153
Our house will be in the sky

41:30.946 --> 41:37.328
We'll hang a sign
Outside the door

41:37.912 --> 41:39.872
"Please…

41:41.874 --> 41:45.169
Do not disturb"

41:48.506 --> 41:49.340
Come on.

41:49.423 --> 41:51.675
-Why?
-Bring your fabric.

41:51.759 --> 41:53.469
And the chemicals. Come.

41:53.552 --> 41:54.720
-Right now?
-Yes.

41:58.891 --> 42:01.060
Come on, get in.
We're gonna hunt flamingos.

42:01.143 --> 42:04.104
I'm scared, Aarón. What flamingos?

42:04.188 --> 42:06.315
More like crocodiles than flamingos.

42:07.233 --> 42:10.236
I mean, you do get
that my flamingo feather design

42:10.319 --> 42:12.071
is nothing more than fantasy?

42:12.154 --> 42:13.864
We don't have to make it real.

42:14.406 --> 42:16.534
Well, that's why. Fantasies are the best.

42:18.285 --> 42:20.621
Trust me. We'll find them.

42:20.704 --> 42:21.789
Then what's the plan?

42:22.414 --> 42:26.335
I mean, you want me to pluck the feathers
of a sleeping flamingo. Is that it?

42:26.919 --> 42:28.504
We already stole the boat.

42:31.215 --> 42:32.633
No, I'm going to steal them.

42:41.517 --> 42:44.562
Hey. Have you found
what you were searching for?

42:46.063 --> 42:47.064
Well…

42:47.565 --> 42:51.110
I came here to set up
a secret, clandestine studio.

42:51.902 --> 42:53.362
I'm writing some songs

42:53.445 --> 42:55.364
that I don't want anyone
to find out about.

42:57.908 --> 43:00.369
It's kind of personal.

43:02.037 --> 43:03.205
How mysterious.

43:03.998 --> 43:04.873
Why?

43:06.542 --> 43:08.836
Because maybe I still
have something to prove.

43:10.546 --> 43:11.880
That I have my own voice.

43:12.464 --> 43:14.133
And that's why you're so set

43:14.216 --> 43:15.926
on me finding my own too?

43:20.431 --> 43:21.599
Look, there's one!

43:23.892 --> 43:25.185
Wow!

43:26.645 --> 43:28.606
It's a flamingo feather!

43:30.899 --> 43:32.526
Wow! It's incredible.

44:27.539 --> 44:28.916
It's incredible!

44:30.542 --> 44:31.502
Thank you.

44:32.336 --> 44:33.921
We've always helped each other.

44:35.089 --> 44:35.923
You and me.

44:37.174 --> 44:38.008
Sara.

44:42.137 --> 44:42.971
I missed you.

44:43.555 --> 44:44.390
And I you.

44:45.891 --> 44:48.268
See, Sara? See how you can want things?

44:52.231 --> 44:54.817
Right now I just want Lucy
to like the dress.

44:54.900 --> 44:56.652
Because if she doesn't, I'll freak.

44:56.735 --> 44:57.945
Lucy.

44:59.321 --> 45:01.407
It's just all this with the ring,
the wedding,

45:01.490 --> 45:03.701
it's going so quick, it was impulsive.

45:05.411 --> 45:06.245
What?

45:07.204 --> 45:10.082
Well, it just went very fast,

45:10.165 --> 45:13.043
but it's all good.

45:19.466 --> 45:21.802
You'll be within me

45:22.511 --> 45:25.639
Until the final beat of my heart

45:25.723 --> 45:28.267
In the light of your balcony

45:28.851 --> 45:32.354
In every minute, at every corner

45:33.230 --> 45:35.441
You'll be within me

45:36.233 --> 45:38.736
Even though we've said goodbye

45:43.657 --> 45:46.744
And in the morning breeze

45:46.827 --> 45:51.874
I mistook your scent for a rose

45:55.919 --> 45:58.672
I awake in the early morning…

45:59.798 --> 46:00.632
You?

46:01.592 --> 46:02.843
Expecting someone else?

46:04.470 --> 46:05.429
You!

46:05.512 --> 46:06.346
Me.

46:06.930 --> 46:07.806
Hey,

46:08.474 --> 46:10.726
I've been thinking a lot,

46:10.809 --> 46:11.894
about lots of things.

46:12.436 --> 46:14.813
And I'm ready to tell you.

46:16.899 --> 46:18.108
-Okay.
-Okay.

46:18.984 --> 46:19.985
Okay.

46:20.068 --> 46:23.572
If you want, let's try one last time.

46:23.655 --> 46:24.490
Okay, yeah.

46:25.783 --> 46:26.867
No. Look.

46:26.950 --> 46:28.243
One last time?

46:28.952 --> 46:30.746
No. What I…

46:31.246 --> 46:33.081
What I wanted to say is…

46:34.708 --> 46:36.376
I'm going to come live in Mérida.

46:37.419 --> 46:38.253
In Mérida!

46:41.799 --> 46:43.926
Oh, wow!

46:44.426 --> 46:47.763
Wow! Okay.

46:48.931 --> 46:50.349
Wow.

46:50.432 --> 46:51.266
Yeah.

46:53.977 --> 46:55.187
Here you are.

46:55.270 --> 46:56.146
I'm gonna change.

46:56.230 --> 46:57.064
Did you tell her?

46:57.147 --> 46:59.274
Did you tell her? I helped.
I picked the ring…

46:59.358 --> 47:00.526
Sara! Don't listen.

47:00.609 --> 47:02.611
-Hey, sir! I don't want to see that.
-No!

47:02.694 --> 47:04.947
-Okay!
-Cover up, my love.

47:06.448 --> 47:07.950
Okay, family.

47:08.033 --> 47:10.786
I have a ton of things to do,
dresses, Fashion Fest,

47:10.869 --> 47:12.538
a wedding to plan, so…

47:12.621 --> 47:13.455
Yeah.

47:13.539 --> 47:14.873
I'm off! Okay?

47:14.957 --> 47:15.791
Yeah.

47:17.209 --> 47:18.377
Hey.

47:18.460 --> 47:19.711
-Go after her!
-Not now.

47:20.921 --> 47:23.048
No, hey, I need you to listen to me.

47:24.216 --> 47:25.634
I need you to listen to me!

47:34.268 --> 47:35.352
You're divine.

47:35.435 --> 47:39.982
Moni, please, a little more volume.

47:40.774 --> 47:41.859
Let's see, Charly.

47:41.942 --> 47:43.443
I don't know what to do with her.

47:43.527 --> 47:44.653
She's too pale.

47:45.737 --> 47:47.906
No. Change everything, please. No.

47:52.578 --> 47:54.621
Rick! The rack, please!

47:54.705 --> 47:55.539
Okay.

47:56.081 --> 47:57.040
Here it is.

48:00.210 --> 48:01.628
I have more in the car.

48:04.590 --> 48:06.717
They're much better than these, I think.

48:10.637 --> 48:12.764
You hate them. Do you hate me?

48:13.390 --> 48:14.391
I'll burn them.

48:14.474 --> 48:16.018
You're brilliant, Sara Escribano.

48:16.852 --> 48:17.811
They're perfect!

48:18.937 --> 48:20.689
-I told you, amore.
-They're alive!

48:21.440 --> 48:22.691
Told you too, Sari.

48:23.650 --> 48:24.985
Congratulations!

48:25.068 --> 48:26.069
Congratulations!

48:26.653 --> 48:29.156
Marina Abramóvich was right.

48:31.658 --> 48:32.534
Hey!

48:32.618 --> 48:34.870
Fire! Sacni, the dresses!

48:34.953 --> 48:35.871
Fuck this!

48:35.954 --> 48:37.122
-I quit!
-The dresses!

48:37.623 --> 48:38.457
Let's go!

48:39.124 --> 48:40.584
Go, quickly!

48:40.667 --> 48:42.419
You're in charge of everything!

48:42.502 --> 48:43.337
-Me?
-Yeah!

48:44.254 --> 48:45.505
What?

48:46.423 --> 48:47.257
What the hell?

48:49.343 --> 48:50.177
Are you okay?

48:51.637 --> 48:54.348
Where is Colavita? Anyone seen Colavita?

48:54.431 --> 48:56.016
-Where is my third outfit?
-Sara?

48:56.725 --> 48:58.185
-What're you doing?
-No, Aarón.

48:58.268 --> 48:59.895
For real, I need five minutes.

48:59.978 --> 49:01.521
-I need to be alone.
-Relax.

49:02.189 --> 49:03.065
-No.
-Breathe, Sara.

49:03.148 --> 49:04.232
Five minutes, guys.

49:04.316 --> 49:05.150
I can't.

49:07.069 --> 49:09.905
No, really. I don't know how to meditate.
Don't make me.

49:09.988 --> 49:10.822
Me neither.

49:11.949 --> 49:14.576
But, before each concert
I do it and it relaxes me.

49:21.959 --> 49:22.793
What's so funny?

49:22.876 --> 49:24.419
Aarón Star gets nervous?

49:24.503 --> 49:26.755
Well, "Aarón Star," no.

49:26.838 --> 49:28.382
But I do.

49:28.924 --> 49:29.758
Look.

49:29.841 --> 49:30.717
I'm shaking.

49:30.801 --> 49:32.094
-No!
-I'm sweating.

49:33.303 --> 49:34.221
Calm down.

49:38.308 --> 49:39.434
What are you doing?

49:39.518 --> 49:40.644
Meditating.

49:41.353 --> 49:44.439
A big round of applause for Aarón Star!

49:49.277 --> 49:51.029
I'm going to chew you up, girl

49:58.370 --> 49:59.371
You're my bubblegum

49:59.955 --> 50:01.832
-Let this flow.
-That's it.

50:01.915 --> 50:03.250
You're my cinnamon gum

50:04.501 --> 50:06.128
Fluff up the dress, Sacni.

50:08.588 --> 50:12.342
You're my cinnamon gum, baby

50:12.426 --> 50:16.096
I won't stop
Until my tongue goes numb

50:18.140 --> 50:21.393
That's it. Grand. Shine, girls.
Like never before!

50:21.476 --> 50:23.061
I'll remove that red dress

50:23.145 --> 50:25.605
With no doubt, kiss your neck

50:25.689 --> 50:27.399
Enjoying it like a bear

50:27.482 --> 50:29.317
Big! Yes! There we go!

50:30.277 --> 50:33.905
Heading direct to the sweet spot
Ignoring the danger

50:33.989 --> 50:36.491
That's it. Yes. He's already going. Copy?

50:37.701 --> 50:39.244
Yes. Preparing Lucy.

50:39.327 --> 50:43.248
-Am I good?
-Let me check this. Okay, yeah. All good.

50:43.331 --> 50:44.374
Ready, Lucy?

50:45.375 --> 50:46.209
Lucy.

50:46.293 --> 50:47.753
-Ready.
-Right, let's go.

50:49.963 --> 50:51.631
Sacni! How exciting!

50:58.805 --> 51:00.474
Bravo, my love!

51:02.809 --> 51:04.644
Ladies and gentlemen,

51:06.480 --> 51:09.816
let's hear it for Aarón Star.

51:09.900 --> 51:11.568
Lucy and Sara Escribano!

51:11.651 --> 51:12.736
Breathe.

51:12.819 --> 51:13.904
Stand up straight.

51:13.987 --> 51:15.155
-This is your moment.
-Me?

51:15.238 --> 51:16.448
-Yes. Ready?
-I'm going?

51:16.531 --> 51:19.284
-Yes, you'll shine.
-Bye, bad karma. Let's go.

51:20.327 --> 51:21.161
Seriously?

51:22.037 --> 51:24.331
-No! How embarrassing.
-Let's go, Sara!

51:25.415 --> 51:26.583
-No, wait.
-Come on!

51:26.666 --> 51:27.584
Come, let's go.

51:28.168 --> 51:29.544
I can't believe it.

51:29.628 --> 51:32.589
And the genius behind all these designs,

51:32.672 --> 51:35.634
a woman with incomparable talent

51:35.717 --> 51:37.636
who's able to brand all the fabrics,

51:37.719 --> 51:39.096
she can do it for all the--

51:39.179 --> 51:41.848
My sister. Sara Escribano!

51:50.232 --> 51:52.234
Come on.

51:52.984 --> 51:55.570
What the fuck is up with this headache?

52:01.910 --> 52:03.995
Oh, bless you.

52:16.216 --> 52:17.050
Aarón?

52:17.801 --> 52:18.635
What?

52:18.718 --> 52:20.762
You'll be within me

52:28.436 --> 52:31.481
Until the final beat of my heart

52:35.402 --> 52:36.486
What is this?

52:37.445 --> 52:40.615
Salamba sirshasana is what this is called.

52:44.452 --> 52:45.495
No, idiot.

52:45.579 --> 52:46.413
What's this?

52:47.664 --> 52:49.207
A gift. What?

52:49.833 --> 52:50.709
You didn't like it?

52:50.792 --> 52:52.961
Why did you hold onto this for so long?

52:53.044 --> 52:54.713
Because it's super special.

52:54.796 --> 52:56.464
Why dedicate your first album to me?

52:57.048 --> 52:59.384
Because I want you to hear--

52:59.467 --> 53:01.428
No. Why do you want to help my hangover?

53:01.511 --> 53:02.470
Look, Sara…

53:03.054 --> 53:05.557
I heard you puking all night.

53:05.640 --> 53:07.893
What the hell is going on in your head?

53:07.976 --> 53:09.311
Nothing is going on, just…

53:10.645 --> 53:12.606
-It just is, Aarón.
-I do.

53:12.689 --> 53:14.274
-I do too.
-Yes!

53:14.357 --> 53:15.192
Well, me too.

53:17.444 --> 53:18.653
Yes!

53:18.737 --> 53:19.654
Yes, what?

53:19.738 --> 53:21.656
Yes, I'll marry you, Roberto!

53:21.740 --> 53:22.949
Yes!

53:23.033 --> 53:24.409
Yes. You. Very good.

53:25.076 --> 53:26.077
Me?

53:28.038 --> 53:29.206
What?

53:29.289 --> 53:31.458
Hey, congratulations, brother-in-law!

53:31.541 --> 53:32.375
Thanks so much.

53:32.459 --> 53:35.337
-Welcome to the family!
-Thanks so much. Yeah.

53:35.420 --> 53:37.047
-That was cool.
-Incredible!

53:37.130 --> 53:40.926
I was really excited about asking.

53:41.009 --> 53:43.762
I mean, saying, "Do you want to marry me?"

53:43.845 --> 53:47.766
I even learned to ask in English,
I'm not gonna lie.

53:50.477 --> 53:51.394
Look at the fans.

53:51.478 --> 53:55.273
Temperature is 35° Celsius in the shade.

53:55.357 --> 53:58.193
Hey, look at that!

53:58.276 --> 53:59.236
Different colors.

53:59.319 --> 54:00.654
Which would you like?

54:00.737 --> 54:02.364
-Thank you.
-Have a nice day.

54:02.447 --> 54:03.281
You too.

54:03.365 --> 54:04.658
-Ta-da!
-No.

54:04.741 --> 54:05.784
I'll be back.

54:07.994 --> 54:10.080
-Thank you. It's lovely.
-Have a nice day.

54:11.456 --> 54:13.166
What a scam.

54:13.250 --> 54:15.502
You should have bought an iPad.
This doesn't work.

54:15.585 --> 54:18.880
Your boyfriend's profile picture is fake.

54:18.964 --> 54:21.424
You can't trust social media.

54:21.508 --> 54:22.509
You're an adult.

54:24.010 --> 54:24.844
He's a scammer.

54:24.928 --> 54:27.264
These photos were taken
from a Swiss tie catalog.

54:27.347 --> 54:29.641
Yeah, Lauterbrunnen ties.

54:30.767 --> 54:32.352
Since when do you speak German?

54:33.186 --> 54:34.145
Since he taught me.

54:35.397 --> 54:36.439
He's Swiss.

54:38.608 --> 54:39.776
He's a model.

54:39.859 --> 54:42.070
He exists and his name is Hans.

54:44.823 --> 54:46.700
Like those crêpes we had.

54:47.242 --> 54:48.827
Which ones?

54:48.910 --> 54:51.871
The ones we used to eat daily.
Remember? Right after marrying.

54:52.580 --> 54:55.375
The ones on the corner
of our first apartment?

54:55.458 --> 54:56.835
With the little sausages?

54:56.918 --> 54:59.004
Remember how the smell
came through the window?

54:59.587 --> 55:00.422
Yeah.

55:04.592 --> 55:06.886
Wanna dance? Does your Swiss man dance?

55:10.015 --> 55:10.974
For old times.

55:12.309 --> 55:13.935
Let's see if I remember.

55:14.019 --> 55:15.937
Of course you remember, you'll see.

55:16.688 --> 55:17.647
Let's see.

55:18.815 --> 55:20.817
This one is a square, right?

55:21.609 --> 55:24.112
A square and a swing, at least.

55:24.195 --> 55:25.864
Now, with energy!

55:29.326 --> 55:32.287
Slow and sensual!

55:33.413 --> 55:35.081
This is really hard.

55:35.165 --> 55:36.166
There it is.

55:36.249 --> 55:37.083
Ready.

55:38.126 --> 55:39.961
Perfect. Don't move too much.

55:40.045 --> 55:40.879
Okay.

55:42.422 --> 55:43.715
There we go.

55:44.466 --> 55:45.342
Ready.

55:45.425 --> 55:46.259
Let's see.

55:50.013 --> 55:52.599
If you want to change anything,
there's still time.

55:54.893 --> 55:55.727
No way.

55:57.020 --> 55:59.981
Or if you want to add anything,
really, I won't be offended.

56:04.569 --> 56:05.403
Really?

56:05.487 --> 56:07.238
Sara, I love it!

56:07.322 --> 56:09.324
It couldn't be more spectacular!

56:09.407 --> 56:10.950
Well, there we go then.

56:11.034 --> 56:11.868
You're the best.

56:13.745 --> 56:16.164
And now, the world is on the verge
of knowing it.

56:16.831 --> 56:18.208
Sara Escribano.

56:24.214 --> 56:27.384
When I looked on Google,
it said to open it like this…

56:27.467 --> 56:28.468
My love, lemme see.

56:28.551 --> 56:30.512
-I'll help you.
-No. I can do it.

56:30.595 --> 56:32.597
-There…
-Pull, you don't have to twist it.

56:32.680 --> 56:33.723
-There.
-Yeah.

56:33.807 --> 56:36.684
-Then, carefully, because the cork is…
-Turn it.

56:36.768 --> 56:38.436
…under a lot of pressure

56:38.520 --> 56:40.438
and can take out an eye.

56:40.522 --> 56:42.524
Point away from you, so you don't hurt…

56:42.607 --> 56:44.943
Look, let me do it. Let's put this here.

56:46.027 --> 56:47.404
Just turn it.

56:50.198 --> 56:51.449
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

56:52.575 --> 56:53.868
To our wedding.

57:01.292 --> 57:02.127
It's good.

57:06.881 --> 57:08.258
Tell me something dirty.

57:11.469 --> 57:12.595
Something dirty like…

57:13.888 --> 57:16.975
Like, sexual? Or like, sexy…

57:17.058 --> 57:19.978
Like coitus, fornication, right?

57:20.061 --> 57:22.689
I mean sex…

57:22.772 --> 57:24.399
Tell me something to turn me on.

57:24.482 --> 57:26.860
Sweaty sex. Sex with sweat.

57:26.943 --> 57:28.653
Sex with sweat.

57:28.736 --> 57:29.946
And since it's Mérida,

57:30.029 --> 57:33.324
it's even hotter, and the humidity factor
comes into play.

57:33.408 --> 57:35.743
And then, we'd be even sweatier, right?

57:35.827 --> 57:38.955
My love, I want to feel you inside me.

57:39.998 --> 57:40.832
Here?

57:41.458 --> 57:43.209
What will it take to get you to play?

57:43.835 --> 57:46.754
-Shit.
-Can't we just have normal sex?

57:46.838 --> 57:48.381
Like that, like before?

57:50.550 --> 57:51.384
Yeah.

57:57.015 --> 57:59.517
You'll be within me

58:06.107 --> 58:07.525
What are you humming, Sara?

58:10.778 --> 58:11.821
The wedding march.

58:12.572 --> 58:13.406
Oh.

58:13.948 --> 58:14.782
Sexy.

58:31.216 --> 58:33.510
-I love him, Sacni.
-Roberto?

58:39.474 --> 58:40.850
I can't do this to Lucy.

58:42.185 --> 58:43.144
Of course.

58:43.228 --> 58:45.313
It's healthier
to organize a double wedding

58:45.396 --> 58:48.858
with your sister, your fiance,
and the love of your life, right?

58:48.942 --> 58:51.486
No. I didn't say anything
about a double wedding.

58:53.238 --> 58:54.072
That's good.

58:56.574 --> 59:00.119
Sacni, I need a time machine
so I can go back to high school.

59:01.246 --> 59:03.623
Everything was perfect then.
That was my moment.

59:04.290 --> 59:05.208
And I let it pass.

59:06.084 --> 59:07.418
Because of your bad karma?

59:14.384 --> 59:16.553
He's about to plan his move to Mérida.

59:16.636 --> 59:17.470
He's coming.

59:17.971 --> 59:19.681
I don't want him to. What do I do?

59:19.764 --> 59:21.724
Leave Roberto to me.

59:22.225 --> 59:24.644
I'm a pro
at getting city slickers to leave.

59:25.687 --> 59:26.646
What will you do?

59:26.729 --> 59:27.855
Hello, my love!

59:29.274 --> 59:30.942
Hello? Sara?

59:31.442 --> 59:32.277
Bobby.

59:34.571 --> 59:36.990
Look, Bobby,
you have to walk here in Mérida.

59:37.073 --> 59:37.991
Okay.

59:38.074 --> 59:42.537
-It is beautiful, but it's so hot!
-Yeah.

59:42.620 --> 59:43.621
Enjoy it, Bobby!

59:43.705 --> 59:49.544
This is the most important time
of the day. Feel the sun on your body.

59:50.169 --> 59:51.796
I mean, a bit of water

59:51.879 --> 59:53.006
and boom!

59:53.673 --> 59:56.342
But, isn't there water?

59:59.554 --> 1:00:00.471
Come on, let's go!

1:00:02.056 --> 1:00:03.474
Don't you know the cenotes?

1:00:04.225 --> 1:00:05.518
-Come on, Bobby.
-Sara?

1:00:06.561 --> 1:00:09.606
Sara's waiting for us,
so you can't stop here.

1:00:10.148 --> 1:00:11.232
-Okay.
-Come on.

1:00:15.653 --> 1:00:18.531
Sara is very late, no?

1:00:18.615 --> 1:00:20.283
Can't we wait in the shade?

1:00:20.992 --> 1:00:22.952
Patience, Bobby.

1:00:23.036 --> 1:00:25.538
In Mérida, time doesn't matter.

1:00:25.622 --> 1:00:27.206
Yeah, but Sara isn't from here.

1:00:27.915 --> 1:00:29.584
She might as well be.

1:00:29.667 --> 1:00:32.670
If you saw how much she's changed
since coming here…

1:00:32.754 --> 1:00:34.255
No, I already noticed.

1:00:34.339 --> 1:00:35.423
Right?

1:00:35.506 --> 1:00:37.342
She's picked up bad habits.

1:00:37.425 --> 1:00:38.843
You wouldn't recognize her.

1:00:41.095 --> 1:00:41.929
Hey.

1:00:44.515 --> 1:00:45.350
What?

1:00:45.433 --> 1:00:49.312
You know what? If you're moving to Mérida,
you should adapt.

1:00:49.395 --> 1:00:51.105
-To Maya?
-And to the heat.

1:00:52.899 --> 1:00:54.734
Well, it's not that bad.

1:00:54.817 --> 1:00:57.654
With air conditioning,
everything is better, no?

1:00:58.279 --> 1:00:59.155
Of course.

1:00:59.238 --> 1:01:00.406
Bad part is the price.

1:01:01.157 --> 1:01:02.075
Is it expensive?

1:01:02.659 --> 1:01:04.786
Where you are, at least 2,000.

1:01:04.869 --> 1:01:06.204
No, 2,000 is okay.

1:01:06.287 --> 1:01:08.081
I can manage 2,000 well.

1:01:08.164 --> 1:01:08.998
Weekly.

1:01:09.582 --> 1:01:10.625
Oh, no.

1:01:10.708 --> 1:01:12.377
And, ice cream?

1:01:12.460 --> 1:01:14.754
If you say it in Maya, it's on me, Bobby.

1:01:16.798 --> 1:01:17.632
Sara?

1:01:21.344 --> 1:01:22.679
This guy's dead.

1:01:26.599 --> 1:01:27.642
I'm alive?

1:01:29.894 --> 1:01:30.812
That's correct.

1:01:32.021 --> 1:01:33.898
Don't worry about the dengue.

1:01:33.981 --> 1:01:34.857
It's not serious.

1:01:39.028 --> 1:01:40.029
I have dengue?

1:01:41.322 --> 1:01:42.448
And heatstroke.

1:01:42.532 --> 1:01:44.826
But you'll survive.

1:01:45.326 --> 1:01:46.160
Ah.

1:01:46.244 --> 1:01:49.080
So, you'll have to learn to live
with my bad karma.

1:01:50.039 --> 1:01:51.290
Bad karma?

1:01:51.374 --> 1:01:54.711
I'm the one under the effects
of strong drugs, Sara.

1:01:56.254 --> 1:01:57.630
I'm being serious, Roberto.

1:01:57.714 --> 1:01:59.465
My life is one string of bad luck.

1:02:03.261 --> 1:02:05.805
Your life with me feels like bad luck?

1:02:06.472 --> 1:02:07.515
No, hold on.

1:02:07.598 --> 1:02:09.976
Don't put words in my mouth
that I haven't said.

1:02:10.768 --> 1:02:14.105
I'm just saying my bad luck
is very contagious.

1:02:14.188 --> 1:02:15.314
Very.

1:02:16.065 --> 1:02:16.899
Sara,

1:02:17.692 --> 1:02:20.611
did you send Sacnité
to scare me out of moving?

1:02:22.822 --> 1:02:25.366
Do you have any idea what I'm sacrificing

1:02:25.450 --> 1:02:27.368
to come live in Mérida with you?

1:02:28.578 --> 1:02:29.412
Well…

1:02:30.079 --> 1:02:32.707
that's exactly why I'm trying to--

1:02:32.790 --> 1:02:33.666
Frighten me?

1:02:33.750 --> 1:02:34.584
No!

1:02:34.667 --> 1:02:35.710
Warn me?

1:02:37.628 --> 1:02:40.339
Sara, I was very happy to come here.

1:02:41.549 --> 1:02:44.051
But I was also afraid that maybe

1:02:44.135 --> 1:02:47.930
our relationship only existed in memories.

1:02:48.514 --> 1:02:50.224
And coming here confirmed it.

1:02:52.602 --> 1:02:53.436
Look, Roberto…

1:02:55.938 --> 1:02:57.482
I love you very much

1:02:57.565 --> 1:02:59.942
and we've always gotten along so well.

1:03:00.902 --> 1:03:02.945
And you're a man who's very…

1:03:03.738 --> 1:03:05.823
Well, very punctual.

1:03:05.907 --> 1:03:07.074
Oh, thanks.

1:03:08.075 --> 1:03:10.161
And very protective, you know?

1:03:10.244 --> 1:03:11.913
-And also--
-Sara, I'm fine.

1:03:14.123 --> 1:03:14.957
I'm happy.

1:03:16.667 --> 1:03:19.504
And I want you to be happy.
You deserve to be happy.

1:03:20.171 --> 1:03:23.466
But you can't be happy

1:03:23.549 --> 1:03:25.802
if you're not where you want to be.

1:03:27.220 --> 1:03:29.347
And you want…

1:03:31.974 --> 1:03:33.309
cinnamon gum.

1:03:36.145 --> 1:03:37.146
And I'm not that.

1:03:40.024 --> 1:03:41.818
I also love you very much, Sara.

1:03:44.278 --> 1:03:46.113
-Sorry!
-No, it's okay.

1:03:46.197 --> 1:03:47.448
-Sorry.
-It's okay.

1:03:50.368 --> 1:03:51.202
Hey,

1:03:52.495 --> 1:03:54.664
the ring you got me is super pretty.

1:03:55.164 --> 1:03:56.123
Thank you.

1:03:57.041 --> 1:03:57.875
Ah.

1:03:59.001 --> 1:04:01.838
Hey, so about the ring,

1:04:03.047 --> 1:04:05.424
would it be an inconvenience
to give it back?

1:04:05.508 --> 1:04:07.343
It's just that it was my grandma's.

1:04:07.426 --> 1:04:09.846
And has been passed
from generation to generation.

1:04:09.929 --> 1:04:11.180
No, I understand perfectly.

1:04:11.264 --> 1:04:13.182
-No need to explain.
-Thank you.

1:04:13.266 --> 1:04:14.809
It's yours.

1:04:14.892 --> 1:04:15.935
-Okay?
-Okay.

1:04:22.608 --> 1:04:25.194
Miss, can you give us five minutes?

1:04:25.278 --> 1:04:27.113
-Of course.
-Just while we break up.

1:04:27.196 --> 1:04:28.281
-Absolutely.
-Yeah?

1:04:28.364 --> 1:04:29.198
Thank you.

1:04:35.329 --> 1:04:36.497
Sara, your hand.

1:04:37.748 --> 1:04:39.375
It's missing the ring!

1:04:41.085 --> 1:04:43.045
Is your wedding canceled, Sara?

1:04:47.174 --> 1:04:48.050
Mmm-hmm.

1:04:49.594 --> 1:04:50.720
My wedding is canceled.

1:04:51.929 --> 1:04:53.389
What happened, Sari?

